  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Put a large baking tray[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span> in the oven to heat up (this will stop the <strong>pizza bottoms </strong>from going soggy!)</p><p>Add your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray, then scrunch the sides up to create a parcel</p><p>Add your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1691151710776-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1691151710776-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1691151710776-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1691151710776-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1691151710776-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 15 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, remove the tray from the oven and set aside to cool in the tin foil parcel – these are your <strong>roasted tomatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1691151719276-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1691151719276-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1691151719276-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1691151719276-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1691151719276-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the tomatoes are roasting, peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the<strong> grated garlic</strong> and 1/3 of your<strong> soft cheese </strong>(save the rest for later!) in a small bowl with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>dried oregano</strong>, 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[6 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>creamy tomato sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1691151723120-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
